#Text=Chapter XV
#Text=A forlorn woman went along a lighted avenue .
#Text=The street was filled with people desperately bound on missions .
#Text=An endless crowd darted at the elevated station stairs and the horse cars were thronged with owners of bundles .
#Text=The pace of the forlorn woman was slow .
#Text=She was apparently searching for some one .
#Text=She loitered near the doors of saloons and watched men emerge from them .
#Text=She scanned furtively the faces in the rushing stream of pedestrians .
#Text=Hurrying men , bent on catching some boat or train , jostled her elbows , failing to notice her , their thoughts fixed on distant dinners .
#Text=The forlorn woman had a peculiar face .
#Text=Her smile was no smile .
#Text=But when in repose her features had a shadowy look that was like a sardonic grin , as if some one had sketched with cruel forefinger indelible lines about her mouth .
#Text=Jimmie came strolling up the avenue .
#Text=The woman encountered him with an aggrieved air .
#Text=" Oh , Jimmie , I 've been lookin ' all over fer yehs -- , " she began .
#Text=Jimmie made an impatient gesture and quickened his pace .
#Text=" Ah , do n't bodder me ! Good Gawd !
